        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>244 West 52.<lb/>
                Dec 14&#47;80<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I hasten to thank you for<lb/> yours of yesterday in answer to mine.<lb/></p>
            <p>I have not enquired of the<lb/> Hazan who assisted&#44; as to the composition<lb/> of his Beth Din&#59; if Mr Salamon took<lb/> Tebilah in presence of the Hazan and<lb/> two others&#44; I presume that must<lb/> suffice&#58; I have not moved in the<lb/> matter after my refusal to participate<lb/> in the making of him a proselyte.<lb/></p>
            <p>He will call upon me&#44; tomorrow aft&#39;noon&#59;<lb/> I shall probably see the Hazan<lb/> above referred to before that&#44; and<lb/> shall ascertain as to Tebilah and<lb/> instruction.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I am instinctively against marrying<lb/> him&#44; but if he has or will have<lb/> conformed to all requirements&#44; I<lb/> presume the marriage will have<lb/> to be performed by me if so desired.<lb/></p>
            <p>Again thanking you for<lb/> your answer and promptness in<lb/> attending&#44; the thoughtfulness of<lb/> which I fully appreciate<lb/></p>
            <p>I am<lb/>
                dear Sir<lb/>
                Yrs vy truly<lb/>
                H. P. Mendes.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                546 North 5th<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa.<lb/></p>
        </body>
